is copying a file considered backing it up?
well, if you copy the file to a different drive entirely
some people consider partitions a way of backing stuff up, but if the drive goes, all partitions go with it.
so you wanna get important things on multiple drives
im asking because a Mod on nexus wants a backup save of my game file just in case it breaks the game
Well, in this case, it's probably a good idea to copy/paste the gamesave somewhere else on your computer
so if the game itself breaks due to what happens in the game
ya thats what i thought ok thanks
then it's probably a good idea to have a backup elsewhere
so you can, you know, not do that thing that broke the game
that's what I do with TerraTech sometimes. save game and let the game's autosave be the source of problems
so if I run into a bug, I can send the devs the autosave and they can see the bug
and I can revert back to the last savepoint I had
and I don't lose that much time :)
and i just kind of avoid the bug
Also, because my savepoint is a specific point in time, I can always start from there and try to replicate the bug
which helps in identifying what could be causing it
